Abstract = {{Software systems evolve continuously, requiring continuous maintenance
   and development. Consequently, their architecture tends to degrade with
   time as it becomes less relevant to new, emerging requirements.
   Therefore, stability or resilience is a primary criterion for evaluating
   an architecture. In this paper, we propose a quantitative approach to
