Pages = {{338-354}},
Abstract = {{To ensure widespread deployment and popularity, next generation wireless
   services will require a Quality of Service (QoS), and particularly a
   reliability, that is independent of the radio transmission medium.
   However, because of the failure-prone nature of wireless networks,
   providing a reliable communication link and guaranteeing a consistent
   QoS to users become key issues. In this tutorial, we describe the most
   common source of failures in wireless networks and provide a systematic
   failure classification procedure. Drawing from the vast literature on
