   transportation initiatives. Although carsharing is becoming increasingly
   a popular alternative transportation mode in North America, it is still
   an under-researched area. Current research is aimed at better
   understanding of the behavior of carsharing users. For every member, a
   two-stage approach microsimulates the probability of being active in any
