   active during a month, the probability of that member using the service
   multiple times using a random utility-based model. The model is
   estimated using empirical data from one of the largest carsharing
   companies in North America. The model estimates reveal that the activity
   persistency of members is positively linked to previous behaviors for up
   to 4 months, and that the influence of previous months weakens over
