   We have previously identified a novel TGF-beta co-receptor, CD109, a
   glycosyl phosphatidylinositol (GPI)-anchored protein that negatively
   regulates TGF-beta signaling. Despite CD109's potential relevance as a
   regulator of TGF-beta action in vivo, the mechanisms by which CD109
   regulates TGF-beta signaling are still incompletely understood.
