   treatment severity and weight loss on the solid product properties were
   identified. The decomposition of hemicelluloses was found to be
   responsible for the significant changes of chemical, physical and
   mechanical properties of the torrefied sawdust, including energy
   content, particle size distribution and moisture absorption capacity.
