Abstract = {{This paper addresses the problem of minimizing the energy consumption of
   IP networks. As traffic demands vary over time, energy savings are
   achieved by adapting traffic routing and node and link sleeping patterns
   while guaranteeing QoS and survivability requirements. Network
   survivability is based on shared protection for single link failures.
   The optimization framework considers a set of time intervals and, to
   guarantee network stability, inter-period limitations are imposed. Both
