   constraints in order to build schedules which maximize resources
   utilization while minimizing cancellations and overtime. In this work, a
   four steps approach is proposed. First, surgery cases are assigned to a
   given day. Second, they are scheduled according to different strategies,
   which are evaluated through a simulation tool in the third step. If
   needed, feedback and rescheduling occur in the fourth step. Uncertainty
